sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant GS as Guardrails Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant InputRails as Input Rails<br/>(Content Safety, Jailbreak,<br/>Injection, PII, Topic)
    participant NLP as NLP Models<br/>(spaCy, Transformers,<br/>FastEmbed)
    participant LLM as Upstream LLM<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OutputRails as Output Rails<br/>(Hallucination, Content Safety,<br/>PII, Self-Check)

    Note over Client, LLM: Flow 1: Chat Completion with Guardrails

    Client->>GS: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP plaintext<br/>Optional Bearer Token

    GS->>InputRails: Apply Input Rails
    InputRails->>NLP: Evaluate message<br/>(in-process, in-memory)
    NLP-->>InputRails: Safety scores / entities

    alt Input Rails PASS
        InputRails-->>GS: Message approved
        GS->>LLM: Forward chat completion<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token (forwarded)
        LLM-->>GS: LLM Response

        GS->>OutputRails: Apply Output Rails
        OutputRails->>NLP: Evaluate response<br/>(in-process, in-memory)
        NLP-->>OutputRails: Safety scores

        alt Output Rails PASS
            OutputRails-->>GS: Response approved
            GS-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP
        else Output Rails FAIL
            OutputRails-->>GS: Response blocked
            GS-->>Client: Safety refusal message<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP
        end
    else Input Rails FAIL
        InputRails-->>GS: Message blocked
        GS-->>Client: Safety refusal message<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP<br/>(no LLM call made)
    end

    Note over Client, LLM: Flow 2: Guardrail Check (No LLM Call)

    Client->>GS: POST /v1/guardrail/checks<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP plaintext
    GS->>InputRails: Apply configured rails
    InputRails->>NLP: Evaluate message<br/>(in-process)
    NLP-->>InputRails: Safety evaluation
    InputRails-->>GS: Rail results
    GS-->>Client: Check results<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP
